 "draftNote": "1 of five queued off a bottom-two lane: Mr_Meat31 (midlane→offlane).",
 "coaching": {
  "headline": "A macro loss — objectives 4.5k-43k with no healer drafted. Sparrow won lane but never grouped, so it didn't translate.",
  "team": "Lost on the map, not in lane. Enemy objective damage was 43k to your 4.5k and you drafted no healer into their Phase. Cuban's Sparrow won his lane outright (favored vs Revenant, yours all game) but went 5/6/1 — one assist all game means he was side-laning while the team lost the objectives that decided it. Goldilocks' Iggy got run over by their Murdock offlane (0/5/3 into 10/4/5). Two fixes: draft some sustain, and contest objectives as a five.",
  "whatShiftedIt": "No sustain and no objective presence — you had no healer vs their Phase and lost the objective war 4.5k-43k. Draft a healer or anti-dive support, and bring your won-lane carry to the objective fights instead of farming a side lane.",
  "perPlayer": {
   "a0c393cc-1437-4bdc-8168-64676ce2166c": "Sparrow won lane outright (favored vs Revenant, yours at every checkpoint) and your spikes were on time (Vanquisher ~25m, Imperator ~36m) — but 5/6/1 with one assist all game means you farmed a side lane while objectives went 4.5k-43k against you. When your lane is that far ahead, group with your lead the moment your Vanquisher is up and convert it into objectives.",
   "16f28434-561f-4f23-9454-40321f4a1ef3": "Iggy offlane, 0/5/3 into their Murdock (10/4/5) — your checkpoints were favored on paper but you never got a completed-item spike and got run over. When the bully across from you is ahead, concede farm and play safe instead of trading into it; wait for your team to group.",
   "10edbf65-457d-48d0-9151-9df5b4fcb40a": "Steel support, 0/7/7 and team-low 8.3k damage — you actually won the Phase lane at every checkpoint, but your only real spike (Warden's Faith ~21m) was the lone bright spot and Steel gave the team no sustain into their healer. This is exactly the game your Belica or Zinx changes.",
   "7c8ab99c-31c5-4ea5-a6fa-e0d6417c3f1b": "The Fey mid, 4/5/5 and team-high 28.5k — yours at every checkpoint vs Renna with your Wraith Leggings spike landing ~19m. You held your end up; the loss was the map around you. Use that won lane to help your team contest the objectives you lost.",
   "a412baf3-dd17-4f89-8ecf-9d0704f3a79e": "Khaimera jungle, 7/7/5 — the Countess matchup tilted theirs from 15 minutes on, and with objectives going 4.5k-43k the jungle needed to set and contest more of them. Build note: no armor (Overlord/Basilisk/Rapture) again — finish that core so you survive the late objective fights."
  }
 },
